nodes.body: If `Nat.ofDigits_mod_eq_head` is not wanted, we can move it inside the proof of `Nat.digits_head`
https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/head.20and.20Nat.2EofDigits.2FNat.2Edigits

Adding two `rfl` lemmas leads to some simplification.  I am not sure if this is a good idea, though.
```lean
@[simp]
theorem List.head_empty : List.head! [] = 0 := rfl

@[simp]
theorem Nat.ofDigits_empty (b : ℕ) : ofDigits b [] % b = 0 := rfl

theorem Nat.ofDigits_mod_eq_head (b : ℕ) (l : List ℕ) : (Nat.ofDigits b l) % b = l.head! %b := by
  induction l <;> simp [Nat.ofDigits, Int.ModEq]

theorem Nat.digits_head {b n : ℕ} (h : b ≠ 1) : (Nat.digits b n).head! = n % b := by
  by_cases hb : 1 < b
  · rcases n with _ | n
    · simp
    · nth_rw 2 [← Nat.ofDigits_digits b n.succ]
      rw [Nat.ofDigits_mod_eq_head _ _]
      exact (Nat.mod_eq_of_lt (Nat.digits_lt_base hb <| List.head!_mem_self <|
          Nat.digits_ne_nil_iff_ne_zero.mpr <| Nat.succ_ne_zero n)).symm
  · rcases n with _ | _ <;> simp_all [show b = 0 by omega]
```

> Adding two `rfl` lemmas leads to some simplification. I am not sure if this is a good idea, though.
> 
> ```lean
> @[simp]
> theorem List.head_empty : List.head! [] = 0 := rfl
> 
> @[simp]
> theorem Nat.ofDigits_empty (b : ℕ) : ofDigits b [] % b = 0 := rfl
> 
> theorem Nat.ofDigits_mod_eq_head (b : ℕ) (l : List ℕ) : (Nat.ofDigits b l) % b = l.head! %b := by
>   induction l <;> simp [Nat.ofDigits, Int.ModEq]
> 
> theorem Nat.digits_head {b n : ℕ} (h : b ≠ 1) : (Nat.digits b n).head! = n % b := by
>   by_cases hb : 1 < b
>   · rcases n with _ | n
>     · simp
>     · nth_rw 2 [← Nat.ofDigits_digits b n.succ]
>       rw [Nat.ofDigits_mod_eq_head _ _]
>       exact (Nat.mod_eq_of_lt (Nat.digits_lt_base hb <| List.head!_mem_self <|
>           Nat.digits_ne_nil_iff_ne_zero.mpr <| Nat.succ_ne_zero n)).symm
>   · rcases n with _ | _ <;> simp_all [show b = 0 by omega]
> ```

Looks like a good idea to me!

Yes, also looks like a good idea to me!
I moved `List.head_empty` to a more appropriate place.
